cal union chartered by an international union or selfchartered established for the purposes of fraud it may have no members the members may be relatives or individuals involved in organized crime rather than workers or the union may claim to represent workers but in fact no relationship has been established the holder of the charter for the paper local charter often enters into a sweetheart contract with an employer or uses it as extortion threatening to unionize the workers unless he receives a payoff paper locals are denounced by the aflcio code of ethical practices see doherty industrial and labor relations terms a glossary  the conglomerate of crime time august    no ordinary hoodlum the new york times august    a b loftus joseph a august   top beck aide links hoffa to phony teamster locals the new york times   raskin teamster units stir new storm the new york times february   raskin hoffa of the teamsters forcing labor showndown the new york times march    ranzal  teamster units face us inquiry the new york times march   kihss peter local chartered with no members the new york times april   kihss teamsters rules appall us judge the new york times april   racketeer is guilty of contempt the new york times may   levey writ restores lacey as teamster leader the new york times may   dio indicted here in union sellout the new york times june   dios locals face charter reviews the new york times june   raskin senators study dio union tiein the new york times september   roth dio and unionist named extorters the new york times october   teamsters spurn dio local order the new york times december   lacey will defy teamster chief the new york times december   raskin dio paper unions offer first dues the new york times december   raskin orourke wins post the new york times january    loftus joseph a january   teamsters aide balks at inquiry on union rackets the new york times   raskin teamsters avoid challenge to us the new york times january   raskin teamsters seek way 